    <!-- About / Motivation -->
    <section id="about">
      <h2>About Me</h2>
      <p>My desire to study healthcare and the medical sciences comes from a very personal place—one shaped by loss, childhood experiences, and a commitment to improving access to medical care for people who need it most.</p>
      <p>I grew up in a rural village where trips to the hospital were rare. My grandmother, who raised me for most of my childhood, shaped my character. People in the village called me “Adwuma ba”—the hardworking child—because I followed her everywhere on the farm.</p>
      <p>Her illness and passing ignited my passion for healthcare. Since then, I have volunteered at hospitals, led health awareness campaigns, and pursued research in microbiology and infectious diseases, determined to make a difference in public health.</p>
    </section>

